features.text:
#  Various Works
## Jensalittleloopy

Chaos artist working in fiber, mixed media/collage, and digital art. On a mission to carve out a path for crafters and makers in the NFT community.

#Lockdown  (Right)

Time didn’t feel like it mattered anymore, the hours just ran together. The only thing we heard outside were the birds. We fed them, built elaborate birdhouses and feeding rituals for them. They rewarded us with song. We wanted to fly away too.

#  Various Works
## Whoiseren

Enter my pixel world of animals who have taken over the planet years after all of the humans vanished. My art discusses friendship, rough childhoods, addiction and understanding yourself while facing the fact that most of our problems repeat but we forget about them when the next generation comes.

#Tripping Rat  (Left)

A light-hearted piece about trying to fit in to society and looking "normal" while dissociating/hallucinating

#  Various Works
## Tahwarts
i am a queer artist from croatia, mainly working in digital 2d art but also in watercolours and fibre arts on the side. art has been a hobby for me for a very long time but through nft i found the courage to share it as pieces of myself. my art most frequently features human-adjacent characters as subjects, such as objectheads and monster girls, through which i attempt to explore small but very human moments.

# Bells (Left)

"""finding a rhythm of motivation can be hard. for her, it wasn't about exercise at first, but through biking she found a song within herself. as she moves, every square of the city she goes through creates another verse in her melody.""

this piece is about finding passion and enjoying life, during every moment of it."

#  Various Works
## Kid Art Projects

Alexa loves to make selfie art, sketches, emotional expressive art, and anything creative with her younger siblings. Passionate, independent, inventive explorer. Alexa is 14 years old and her NFT art is currently curated by her father Joe McCabe at her family's website: https://KidArtProjects.com

# I Love You

A doodle by 14 year old Alexa in 2021. Made with love. 😘

# Various Works
## Queer NFT

An established artist claiming an NFT space for queer expression. The commercial world of art has held our community back, prevented us from showing work that reflects 100% of who we are. So I am here now, sharing my hidden works with the world as NFT.

#  Queer NFT; Series 3; No. 6 (Right)

 From my NFT Series 3, a 16 painting abstraction study using snapchat submitted pics to explore a lighter side of the penis, on oil on canvas.  Number six in the series explores both texture and compositional solid vs void.

# Various Works
## Trygve Skogrand

I have been working with digital art since the late 1990. I have had the computer as my main artistic tool since then and mainly work with collage and digital paintings. In my art I seem to be looking for glimpses of answers to the question “What is it like to be human? Isn’t it strange, to be a spiritual creature and a piece of nature?” I live and work just beside a large forest in Trondelag, Norway, and find this a peaceful and inspiring location for making art.

# Invisibled (Left)

"The work ""Invisibled"" is from a series of digital photo collages called the ""Theatre of Shame"". The works consists of constructed human figures, made from multiple self-portraits, placed into dreamlike, surreal landscapes. 

The subject for the series is prejudice and shame. It is easy and natural to unconsciously inherit the values and prejudices of the society one lives in. That is sadly even true when the prejudices are against yourself, against you own sub-groups of society, creating shame about who you are and what you are created to be. The artist has used is personal experiences as a homosexual as the starting point for the series.

The work ""Invisibled"" shows a figure hiding in a misty and unclear landscape. The figure is covered in multiple eyes, looking for danger, looking for a way out, looking to be seen."

# Various Works
## Angelo Creates (Right)

AngeloCreates is a multimedia artist from Denver, CO whose work plays with the aesthetics of drag culture in otherworldly — and underworldly — settings.

# Eyes Up Here

Rebecca (they/them) up close. Don't forget their eyes are up there. Created in 3D. Inclusive alien. 2020 3D/Photography, Forger app, Substance Painter, Adobe Dimension. Photo taken in Highlands Ranch, Colorado USA. Alien Sculpted in Denver, Colorado. 100 editions for 1 $xtz

# Various Works
## Riot Deleted (Left)

I'm Riot. A trans nb artist who works with AI for their art. I look at how bodies, self-expression and queer identities changes with technology and create visual love letters to identities and queer bodies. I work with machine learning, and am currently training a GAN (HypGal) to take care of my tweeting for me.

# Dysphoria

A state of feeling very unhappy, uneasy, or dissatisfied. dysphoria is a video and associated AR filter experience where the audience can be both the viewer and the viewed

# Various Works (Continues on inner wall)
## Ego Rangel (Right)
I'm an artist from the city of Tijuana, Mexico who is currently studying arts and film careers. My work transits between the social and the personal, talking about topics such as family, union and creating an identity within a patriarchal society where men are emotionally castrated. 

# IAME

Digital illustration created from an old photograph where faces and space are blurred, leaving only the characters and certain objects related to the scene to establish a personal relationship with a past absent in my memory.

# Various Works
## Dehiscence Art (Right)

I combine, human anatomy with botanical, animal and pop culture elements to create visual anthropological tales of the human experience. My art is inspired by the line between science fact and science fiction and each artwork has a message. They speak to equality, justice, human rights and medical ethics. I hope my artwork can encourage discussion around racial, gender and sexual biases and will allow the viewer to openly negotiate the emotional and gendered meanings of the human body.
